<H3> <TI>   Kebich's Presidential Bid Reportedly Backed Under Pressure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kebich's Presidential Bid Reportedly Backed Under Pressure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0405092794 Minsk RID in Russian 0730 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0405092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk RID </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Is Brest Oblast the `Cradle' of </F>
Statehood?"] 
  [Text] At some enterprises in the city of Kobryn, the 
collection of signatures in support of the main contender for 
the presidential chair, Vyacheslaw Kebich, is being conducted by 
management itself. Appropriate directives have been given to 
heads of workshops and foremen. Workers have been given a 
choice: Either to put their signatures supporting the 
"formidable" candidate or to face difficulties promised by 
managers. Under conditions of general job reductions, many 
prefer to avoid problems. 
  Thus, the Brest Oblast may successfully continue its "good" 
traditions and become once again the "cradle" of a new head of 
state, as it was with Slyunkow [secretary of the Communist Party 
of Soviet Belarus] and Dzemyantsey [former Supreme Soviet 
speaker]. 

</TEXT>

