<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows 12 Percent Pin Hopes on Presidential Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows 12 Percent Pin Hopes on Presidential Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0305085294 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1600 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0305085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed BELAPAN report: "On Some Results of a Poll"] </F>
  [Text] A group of sociologists, headed by Academician 
Babosaw, included a question on presidential elections in a poll 
that was conducted among the workers of 15 largest industrial 
enterprises of Belarus. Some 53 percent assured that they will 
participate in the elections. Around 28 percent considered that 
the elections of a president authorized with wide powers will 
have no impact on the improvement of the economic situation in 
Belarus. Over 10 percent of the industrial workers stated 
categorically that they will not participate in presidential 
elections. Only 12 percent of the respondents pin their hopes 
for improvement of living standards on the presidential 
elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

