<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   KGB Chief Outlines Primary Goals of Restructured Service </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KGB Chief Outlines Primary Goals of Restructured Service </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0405081394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0700 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0405081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The management and personnel of the Belarusian KGB 
held a conference connected with the decision to alter the KGB's 
structure and the size of its staff. As KGB Chairman Henadz 
Lavitski pointed out in a speech, the goal of the reform is to 
bring the KGB structure in line with the main purpose of the 
special service and its current demands, as well as to avoid any 
improper functions. The main trends of Belarusian KGB 
activities will be conducting intelligence and 
counterintelligence operations, as well as providing the 
authorities with information necessary for adopting resolutions 
at the state level. The KGB will also participate in 
implementing a state program for combating crime, coordinating 
its activities with other law enforcement bodies and strictly 
adhering to its responsibilities and existing legislation. 

</TEXT>

