<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President, Parliament Disagree on Presidential Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President, Parliament Disagree on Presidential Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305112394 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1000 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] With 35 votes in favor and 31 against, the Riigikogu 
readopted today in an unamended form the law on presidency, 
which the president had failed to promulgate. In his 
resolution, President Lennart Meri referred to the law on 
presidency being in conflict with the Constitution because the 
law on presidency allows the prime minister the right to be the 
first to decide whether state requirements are urgent. The 
Riigikogu first adopted the law on presidency on 23 March this 
year, and the president failed to promulgate it [words 
indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

