<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Claims Russian Officers Planning Armed Coup </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Claims Russian Officers Planning Armed Coup </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0305105694 Tallinn ETA in English 0727 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0305105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From 3 May HOMMIKULEHT, p 1; "News Bulletin" No. 84] </F>
  [Text] MP [member of parliament] Mart Niklus, vice 
chairman of the Independent faction, presented a report of the 
Defence League Tartu unit of a secret meeting of Russian 
officers held in Tartu on 23 April and concerning the 
organisation of an armed coup. 
  The plans concern all Estonia's regions and the conspirators 
have the necessary armament, Niklus told yesterday's traditional 
picket at the Russian Naval HQ. The intended date is not known 
yet, he admitted. 
  Niklus added that subversive groups are located in several 
towns and they intend to present their actions to the 
international public as a civil war, which would justify the 
intervention of the Russian Army. 
  Niklus also claimed that the evacuation of the Paldiski 
nuclear reactors will cost the Estonian taxpayers 10 million 
kroons and called for the suspension of granting residence 
permits to aliens until the completion of the troops withdrawal. 
  Riigikogu [parliament] Vice Chairman Tunne Kelam later 
dismissed the call, explaining that the suspension would be an 
unreasonable act. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

