</HEADER>

<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   28 Reported HIV-Positive; 1 AIDS Carrier </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    28 Reported HIV-Positive; 1 AIDS Carrier </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0405074894 Tallinn ETA in English 1849 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0405074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] In Estonia there are, at present, 28 HIV-infected 
people and one person who has developed AIDS, Jaan Martin from 
the State AIDS Centre told ETA, on Tuesday [3 May]. Martin said 
that a total of 34 virus-infected people have been registered in 
Estonia, the first already in 1988. Three of the infected have 
left Estonia and two have died, which leaves us with 28 infected 
and one who has developed AIDS. All infected have got their 
infection through sexual relations. 
  According to different estimates about 2.5 million people in 
the whole world have developed AIDS, of which 850,000 have been 
registered officially. HIV infected amount to about 14 million. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

