<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tbilisi Chief Says Police `Forced' To Turn to Crime </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tbilisi Chief Says Police `Forced' To Turn to Crime </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305173394 Tbilisi SVOBODNAYA GRUZIYA in Russian 26 Apr 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU0305173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi SVOBODNAYA GRUZIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["BS-Press" report under rubric "According to Reports From </F>
Correspondents and Information Agencies": "The Tbilisi Police 
Garrison Is in Need of Help"] 
  [Text] Addressing a meeting of heads of law enforcement 
bodies in Georgia, Tbilisi Police Chief Demur Mikadze stated 
that 600 policemen had not been paid at all for eight months and 
[these] people "were being forced to take up arms and rob." 
  Since the beginning of this year, 28 police employees had 
been dismissed from the internal affairs bodies for various 
offenses and criminal proceedings had been initiated in eight 
cases. He pointed out other problems affecting the Tbilisi 
police garrison: the lack of a material and technical base, 
modern equipment, and essential means to fight crime. 

</TEXT>

