Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Issues Market Prices Order </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Issues Market Prices Order </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904210694 Yerevan SNARK in English 1409 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2904210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 29 April (SNARK) -- The head of Georgian 
state, Eduard Shevardnadze, issued an order according to which 
the number of state-funded facilities will be reduced since the 
second quarter of 1994. The order also reads that, with purpose 
of fast transition to free prices, the state subsidiaries for 
bread, electric power and gas are planned to be cut. 
  At the same time, VAT [value-added tax], customs taxes and 
excise duty for petrol will be increased. The 8-percent tax for 
products export will be removed. Also the obligatory currency 
sale to government by the enterprises is no more valid. 
  The order, as think the government specialists, has been 
developed according to the IMF and IBRD [International Bank for 
Reconstruction and Development] recommendations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

