<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Removal of Ordubadskiy Leader Protested </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Removal of Ordubadskiy Leader Protested </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305194494 Baku TURAN in English 1731 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0305194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nakhichevan, 31 May (TURAN)--On May 2 at 11 o'clock 
the leadership of Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic headed by the 
Chairman of Supreme Majlis, Namik Gasanov, and Premier, 
Shamsaddin Khanbabayev, arrived in Ordubadskiy -- the region 
centre of the republic. 
  The People's Deputy, Khidzhran Kerimli, told TURAN that 
several "Ikarus" buses with armed policemen arrived in 
Ordubadskiy too. The same source reports that President Aliyev 
issued a decree concerning the removal of the head of Executive 
Power of Ordubadskiy, Rovshan Shafiyev (supporter of Elchibey), 
from his duties. 
  Having known about the authorities' intention, Ordubadskiy's 
citizens began to picket the building of Executive Power and 
they protested against President Aliyev's resolution. The talks 
between Nakhichevan's leadership and local authorities lasted 
for 8 hours but were failure. The population and Nakhichevan's 
powers did not agree to fulfill President Aliyev's resolution. 
After that the leadership of Autonomous Republic and policemen 
left Ordubadskiy. 
  As is known, Ordubadskiy's region of Nakhchivan is the only 
region in Azerbaijan where Abulfaz Elchibey's supporters hold 
several offices. After June events last summer Elchibey 
together with its supporters left Baku and arrived at the 
village of Keleki of Ordubadskiy region where he lives until 
now. Since that time Baku several times attempted to remove the 
head of Executive power of Ordubadskiy from his duties but those 
attempts failed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

