  [Text] Baku, 3 May (AZERTAC) -- The Azerbaijani Defense 
Ministry has reported that following three days of relative 
calm, Armenia's Armed Forces resumed their attacks in the north 
of Karabakh on 3 May. 
  The enemy is attacking the Azerbaijani Army's positions in 
Agdamskiy and Terterskiy Rayons with the support of armored 
vehicles. Fierce battles are continuing in some sectors of the 
front. The Azerbaijani fighters are successfully repulsing the 
enemy's attacks. Some 50 enemy soldiers were killed, one tank 
was destroyed, and six heavy machine guns were seized in one 
sector of the front alone. 

