<F P=103> LD0405093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hostilities resumed at daybreak today in the area of 
the Karabakh conflict after a relative lull lasting one day. 
  An ITAR-TASS correspondent has been told by the Karabakh 
army's press service that Azeri troops supported by armor 
attempted to break though the defensive lines of the Karabakh 
forces in the northeast, in the Agdam sector. After a 90-minute 
long battle, all the attacks of the Azeri side were repelled, 
the press service noted. According to the source, the Azeris 
sustained significant losses in manpower and were forced to 
retreat to their initial positions. There were no losses on the 
Karabakh side. 
  According to reports from Stepanakert, the headquarters of 
the Karabakh army is receiving information about a massive 
concentration of Azeri troops and combat hardware in the north 
of Mardakertskiy Rayon. 

