<H3> <TI>   Baltic Presidents Meet in Closed Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baltic Presidents Meet in Closed Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305095194 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
0900 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Presidents of Latvia, Lithuania, and Estonia are 
meeting at the Latvian resort of Jurmala today. The agenda of 
the presidents' closed meeting includes: the Russian-Latvian 
agreement on the withdrawal of Russian troops and future policy 
toward Russia, the Polish-Lithuanian treaty on good-neighborly 
relations, and other political matters. 
  The presidents will meet in private without even their 
advisers present. A Baltic News Service correspondent learned 
in Jurmala, where the presidents are holding the meeting, that 
they are not going to hold a news conference, although a joint 
statement could be released. 
  Final arrangements for the meeting and the topics for 
discussion were made by Presidents Guntis Ulmanis, Algirdas 
Brazauskas, and Lennart Meri by phone yesterday. 
  The meeting was provisionally planned for an earlier date, 
but it was decided to hold it following the visit to Moscow by 
Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis. 

</TEXT>

