<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ambassador Discusses U.S. Economic Aid, Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassador Discusses U.S. Economic Aid, Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0305105394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1900 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0305105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Oleh Bilous, Ukrainian ambassador to the United 
States, has met with Nicholas (Bergs), U.S. National Security 
Council director. During their conversation, the officials 
concentrated on the implementation of economic agreements 
reached during the official visit of Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk in the United States in March of this year. In 
particular, they talked about the next visit of the U.S. [word 
indistinct] economic delegation to Kiev. Nicholas (Bergs) 
briefed the Ukrainian ambassador on plans and the agenda of the 
American delegation in Kiev. During the negotiations in Kiev, 
it is expected that problems will be discussed at the highest 
level related to the progress of economic reforms in Ukraine and 
U.S. aid intended to solve those problems. The Ukrainian and 
American officials will consider and try to agree upon specific 
terms and forms for extending financial and economic aid to 
Ukraine to implement concrete economic projects as part of the 
development of the market economy. Major emphasis at the next 
negotiations in Kiev will be put on issues related to 
intensifying trade between both countries and acceleration of 
U.S. investments into Ukrainian economy. 

</TEXT>

