<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Officials Begin Talks With U.S. Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Officials Begin Talks With U.S. Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405083894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0818 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 4 TASS -- Russian defence officials are 
holding talks today with a U.S. military delegation which 
arrived in Moscow on Tuesday. The U.S. delegation to the talks 
held in the Russian Defence Ministry is led by the U.S. defence 
secretary's aide for issues of nuclear security, Ashton Carter. 
Russia is represented by a working group consisting of officers 
and generals of the general staff and main departments of the 
Defence Ministry. The Russian delegation is led by 
Lieutenant-General Gennadiy Ivanov, aide of the Russian defence 
minister for military politics. 
  The two-day talks are devoted to the discussion of further 
steps to improve coordination and strengthen confidence between 
the defence departments of the two countries, sources from the 
Russian Defence Ministry told ITAR-TASS. 

</TEXT>

