<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Decrees Examination of St Petersburg Election </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Decrees Examination of St Petersburg Election </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0305095194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 30 Apr 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM0305095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation Federal Assembly State Duma decree No. </F>
99-1, signed by I.P. Rybkin, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly State Duma, and dated 22 April 1994: "On 
Elections to the St. Petersburg City Assembly"] 
  [Text] Expressing concern over the results of the 
elections to the St. Petersburg City Assembly, which did not 
lead to the election of the aforesaid organ of representative 
power, and also over the violations of citizens' electoral 
rights, and taking into consideration the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly State Duma Address on Ensuring the Electoral 
Rights of Citizens During Elections to the Legislative 
(Representative) Organs of State Power of Components of the 
Russian Federation and Organs of Local Self-Government dated 25 
February 1994, the Russian Federation Federal Assembly State 
Duma decrees: 
  1. To instruct the Russian Federation Prosecutor's Office 
and the Russian Federation Central Electoral Commission to 
examine the question of compliance with legislation and 
implementation of court decisions by the mayor of the city of 
St. Petersburg during the elections to the St. Petersburg City 
Assembly in March 1994. 
  2. On the basis of the results of the examination of the 
aforesaid question, to instruct the Russian Federation president 
to adopt the necessary measures in respect of officials of the 
city of St. Petersburg. 
  [signed] I.P. Rybkin, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly State Duma 
  [dated] Moscow, 22 April 1994 
  No. 99-1 

</TEXT>

