<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Minister, French Advisor Praise Union With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Minister, French Advisor Praise Union With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0405092994 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1637 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0405092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As BELAPAN learned, Mikhail Marynich, Belarusian 
deputy minister for external economic relations, received today 
Jean-Joseph (Boillo), the economic adviser for Central and 
Eastern Europe at the French Embassy in Prague. During their 
conversation, both officials discussed issues related to the 
condition of Belarusian-French trade and prospects for its 
development. As its positive factor, Mr. (Boillo) pointed to 
the Belarusian-Russian monetary merger agreement and, among 
others, the results of the customs union between Russia and 
Belarus. According to both sides, trade between Belarus and 
France will only gain by the introduction of common customs 
tariffs on the Belarusian-Russian border. Mikhail Marynich 
emphasized that as a result of the customs union with Russia, a 
range of Western countries will view Belarus as a springboard 
for entering the Russian market, which, in the opinion of M. 
Marynich, will serve the Belarusian economy well. 

</TEXT>

