<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk, French Envoy Discuss Regional Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk, French Envoy Discuss Regional Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0305150694 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0305150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk has received 
Alain Lamassoure, French minister delegate for European affairs. 
The officials held a conversation that raised a number of 
important issues related to the further development of 
Ukrainian-French cooperation. For Ukraine, the president 
emphasized, relations with European states, (?including) France, 
are very important. This is why Ukraine appreciates so much 
France's attitude toward the trilateral declaration signed by 
our state [words indistinct]. We also appreciate efforts by 
France, and its president, Francois Mitterrand, to help Ukraine 
destroy nuclear weapons as well as develop its nuclear power 
engineering system and liquidate the consequences of the 
Chernobyl nuclear power plant accident. 
  Following the meeting with the president, most of which was 
held without media representatives, the guest answered questions 
from journalists. In particular, he emphasized that in his 
opinion, there are no differences between the French and 
Ukrainian points of view on the danger of instability on our 
continent. We, Alain Lamassoure declared, are for a Europe 
serving as the center of peace, stability, and prosperity so 
that relations among states are based on equality, democratic 
principles, and friendship, and so that there are no blocs 
forming on European territory. France itself, the guest 
continued, came up with an initiative to hold a conference on 
problems of stability and security in Europe, at which 
representatives of those countries could discuss these problems. 
[Words indistinct] confirmation of Leonid Kravchuk that your 
country will participate in this conference and work there 
constructively. The meeting was attended by Michel Peissik, 
French ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary to Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

