<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Maritime Kray Duty-Free Zone To Attract Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Maritime Kray Duty-Free Zone To Attract Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0305123594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 30 Apr 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM0305123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Base for Foreign Capital"] </F>
  [Text] The country's first duty-free zone [svobodnaya 
tamozhennaya zona] is to be set up in Maritime Kray near the 
Russo-Chinese border. 
  Unlike ordinary duty-free zones, this zone will be a border 
territory, where imports can be brought in and stockpiled 
without payment of duty. Profit from the deal between buyer and 
seller will go to the local administration budget and to the 
Customs Administration account. It is also planned to organize 
processing facilities within the duty-free zone. It is proposed 
that the customs zone be located on the site of a loss-making 
enterprise in Ussuriysk city. The zone will make it possible 
for Maritime Kray to become a major staging post for foreign 
capital on Russia's Pacific seaboard. 

</TEXT>

