<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baltic Presidents Hold Talks in Latvia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meri, Ulmanis Pleased With Polish Pact </H4>

<F P=102> WS0505092094 Tallinn BNS in English 1800 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0505092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, May 04, BNS -- Estonian President Lennart 
Meri and Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis are positive about the 
friendship and cooperation treaty that was signed by their 
Lithuanian and Polish counterparts in Vilnius last week, the 
Lithuanian president's spokesman, Nerijus Maliukevicius, said. 
  The presidents of the three Baltic states met in Latvia 
Tuesday [3 May] for a discussion of troop withdrawal and Baltic 
cooperation issues. Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas 
returned to Vilnius Wednesday. The summit was strictly 
confidential. 
  In an interview with Lithuanian TV, Brazauskas said 
Lithuanian and Latvian views on relations with Russia are quite 
close, while Estonia's position is different, but he declined to 
disclose its essence. 

</TEXT>

