<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Appoints Social Security Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Appoints Social Security Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405144094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1343 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 4 May (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin has signed a decree appointing Lyudmila Bezlepkina as 
minister of social security of the Russian Federation. 
  Prior to this appointment, Lyudmila Bezlepkina was a first 
deputy minister of social security of the Russian Federation. 

