<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suspected Corrupt Officials Detained </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Suspected Corrupt Officials Detained </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405133194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1243 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 4 May (ITAR-TASS) -- The Russian Federal 
Counterintelligence Service has detained officials from the law 
enforcement bodies suspected of corruption. ITAR-TASS has 
learned from well-informed sources that among those detained are 
a senior official of the directorate for administering 
punishments of the Moscow Oblast Main directorate of internal 
affairs, a senior officer of the investigating committee of the 
Russian Interior Ministry, and a Moscow lawyer. 
  Being "kept" by Moscow criminal groupings, by using their 
contacts with corrupt officials from the law enforcement bodies 
and by using bribes in hard currency, they secured the release 
of members of criminal groupings who had committed burglaries, 
robberies, hostage-taking, murders, and other crimes. 
  During the operation, illegal firearms, several hundred 
thousand U.S. dollars, gold, and precious stones were 
confiscated from the suspects. 
  The criminal case involving the individuals is being 
investigated by the Russian General Procuracy. 

</TEXT>

