<H3> <TI>   Fourth Block of Kolskiy Nuclear Power Station Closed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fourth Block of Kolskiy Nuclear Power Station Closed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405192794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1819 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today at 12:00 pm the fourth reactor of the Kolskiy 
Nuclear Power Station was closed down due to a technical fault 
in the security system. Currently, the energy block is 
functioning at one percent of capacity. However, the fourth 
block can be repaired only after the third one, which stopped at 
the end of 1993, renews its work. The first and the second 
blocks were temporarily closed down about four months ago. 
  A working commission has been set up on the Kolskiy Nuclear 
Power Station. It is expected to give an expert evaluation of 
the condition of the reactor which is out of order, an Interfax 
correspondent learned. 

</TEXT>

