<H3> <TI>   Defense Industry Workers Seek Soskovets Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Industry Workers Seek Soskovets Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405140994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1304 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the defense-related plants which 
are on a standby for a strike after two days of picketing of the 
Government House in Moscow at the end of April are pressing for 
a meeting with First Vice Premier Oleg Soskovets, Aleksandr 
Ilyin of the industrial trade unions told Interfax. 
  In his words, First Deputy Defense Minister Andrey Kokoshin 
in a telephone conversation with union leader Sergey Shuklin had 
said that a solution to the industry's problems rested with the 
Prime Minister or his First Deputy. 
  Defense industry workers are pressing the government for 
clearing its debt of more than 170 billion rubles and resolving 
the problem of non-payments as well as pressing for tax cuts. 
  Ilyin said that most of the industry's workforce had to go 
on 
forced leave from May 1. He spoke of stoppages being announced 
until May 11 at nine of ten plants in the Vladimir Region and 
seven out of eight plants in Nizhnyy Novgorod Region. Similar 
plants in Chapayevsk (Samara region) will not resume work until 
May 15. 

</TEXT>

