<H3> <TI>   Atomic Weapons Museum Shows `Original' Hydrogen Bomb </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Atomic Weapons Museum Shows `Original' Hydrogen Bomb </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405211594 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405211594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Moscow Russian Television Network in 
Russian at 1920 GMT on 4 May carries a video report by L. 
Shesterkina on the atomic weapons museum at (Snezhensk), 
formerly known as Chelyabinsk 70. The museum shows "the most 
powerful air-delivered hydrogen bomb in the world" which is, 
Shesterkina stresses, the original weapon, and not a model. 
Parts of decommissioned ballistic missiles and explosive 
devices for civilian purposes are also shown. 

</TEXT>

