<DOCNO> FBIS4-61230 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov087_b_94025" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-087 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Guard Training Center Attacked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Guard Training Center Attacked </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405140594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1318 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Makhachkala May 4 TASS -- A group of armed 
extremists attacked a training centre of the Russian border 
troops in Makhachkala, capital of Daghestan [Dagestan], last 
night. 
  The attackers armed with firearms penetrated the territory 
of 
the centre, but were seized by its guards. They were then 
handed over to the local law enforcement bodies. 
  The press centre of the Russian border troops told ITAR-TASS 
that this is not the first such case in Daghestan where the 
Russian border is now being established. 

</TEXT>

