<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   CIS Military Official Seriously Injured </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CIS Military Official Seriously Injured </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405130994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1252 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yelena Gorelova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 4 TASS -- Chief of staff for military 
cooperation between CIS member-states, Viktor Samsonov, 53, was 
seriously injured in a traffic accident late on May 2, ITAR-TASS 
learned from the press service of the traffic police. 
  The accident occurred within the distance of one kilometer 
as 
Samsonov's car "Volga" with his family entered the Ilyinsk 
highway, returning from Barvikha in the Moscow countryside. 
  A woman-driver in the oncoming Zhiguli car failed to keep 
the 
wheel, drove into the opposite side of the highway for the 
oncoming traffic and the Zhiguli collided with Samsonov's car. 
As a result of the collision Samsonov received numerous 
injuries and bone fractures, his wife was badly injured in the 
face and his son, a student of the Suvorov Military School, had 
a concussion and his nose broken. 
  The woman-driver responsible for the accident was taken to 
hospital, suffering from numerous bone fractures, and her 
companion riding in the same car was instantly killed. 

</TEXT>

