<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khasbulatov Meets With Chechnya's Villagers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khasbulatov Meets With Chechnya's Villagers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405120194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1100 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "Ordinary people have always and everywhere 
understood me," announced former head of the RF Supreme Soviet 
Ruslan Khasbulatov during his meeting with residents of the 
Chechen village of Alkhan-Kala situated ten kilometers from 
Groznyy. 
  As our Interfax correspondent reports, thousands of citizens 
from nearby villages, elders, leaders of the clergy and local 
councils attended. Amateur artists performed at the meeting. 
  Khasbulatov expressed his recognition for the support both 
to 
the village residents and citizens of Chechnya and Russia. 
  Khasbulatov received a gun and Astrakhan sheep-skin hat, a 
papakha, from the village residents. 
  The day before one of the streets in the village of 
Alkhan-Kala was called Imran, the name of Khasbulatov's father. 
Leaders of the local council explained to our Interfax 
correspondent that from 1934-37 Imran Khasbulatov headed the 
local collective farm. 
  Due to the growth of Khasbulatov's popularity in Chechnya, 
observers do not rule out the possibility that he could head the 
forces in opposition to President Johar Dudayev. In particular, 
the present leaders of the opposition welcomed the return of the 
ex-speaker of the Russian parliament to his homeland as they 
connect their hopes for political changes in the republic with 
his name. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

