  [Text] Tula -- Staffers of the Tula Internal Affairs 
Administration's Administration for Combating Organized Crime 
have detained an inhabitant of one of the Baltic countries who 
brought 20 "TT" pistols to Tula for sale. 
  As V. Podolskiy, chief of the Administration for Combating 
Organized Crime, reported, the majority of arms on sale are 
produced in local plants, though some are imported. Over the 
four months of this year more arms have been confiscated than 
during the whole of last year. 

