<H3> <TI>   Chavusy Tank Base Closed, Cleared Out Ahead of Schedule </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chavusy Tank Base Closed, Cleared Out Ahead of Schedule </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0505104694 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1530 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0505104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As BELAPAN has learned, the 1,336th central tank 
reserve base in Chavusy, Mahilyow Oblast, has been liquidated 
four months ahead of a previously established deadline. Around 
1,000 pieces of tank equipment have been transported by 24 
trains to either the Barysaw tank repair plant for dismantlement 
or temporarily to the 969th central tank reserve base in 
Urechcha, Minsk Oblast. 
  Although the Chavusy base was initially scheduled to be 
liquidated by 1 September 1994, the last three temporary-service 
soldiers were released to the Reserves on 30 April. 

</TEXT>

