<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chisinau Restores Ties With Tiraspol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chisinau Restores Ties With Tiraspol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405115994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1100 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moldova's Deputy Premier Valentin Kunev regards as 
possible the restoration of financial and economic relations 
between Kishinev [Chisinau] and Tiraspol in their former volume. 
There is every chance for that, he said in an interview with 
INTERFAX on Wednesday. 
  In his opinion, the recent top-level talks between Moldova 
and Transdniestria "have created a political situation that 
makes it possible to do it." He disclosed that Moldova's 
National Bank would unveil its office in Transdniestria shortly, 
and through this body "a system of mutual crediting would be 
devised and put to work." 
  As he put it, "by launching a mechanism of mutual accounts," 
Kishinev and Tiraspol will be able to "resolve the issues that 
have piled up in power engineering, communication, and other 
fields." In his words, "common approaches have been found to 
how the Tiraspol airport should operate." "Moldova, Kunev said, 
is ready to help reopen it the best it can, but only after the 
Tiraspol authorities persuade the 14th Russian Army, controlling 
the military airport, to make it municipal property. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

