<H3> <TI>   New Party of Communists Registered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Party of Communists Registered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405193394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1834 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] 4 May TASS -- Moldavia [Moldova] 
registered a new political party on Wednesday, the Party of 
Communists of Moldavia. 
  Party co-Chairman Vladimir Voronin said that his party will 
start its activity with re-registering members of the former 
Communist Party who want to resume their membership. 
  Voronin said that the party will soon open sections in 
regions to gain support for the upcoming local elections. He 
believes that party may count on success. 
  Voronin, former interior minister removed by the popular 
front in 1990, said that the recent victory of the Socialist 
Party has shown that people are tired of ethnic upheavals and 
want to have politicians who can ensure stability. 

</TEXT>

