<H3> <TI>   Attends Kyrgyz Constitutional Court Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attends Kyrgyz Constitutional Court Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405202294 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kyrgyz </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] An enlarged meeting of the constitutional court 
of the Kyrgyz Republic was held on 4 May. Askar Akayev, 
President of the Kyrgyz Republic, and Prime Minister Apas 
Dzhumagulov took part in the meeting. Also taking part in the 
meeting's work were the members of the law division of the 
commissions of the supreme and arbitration court, 
representatives of the Ministry of Justice, the procurator, and 
of the Internal Affairs Ministry. President Askar Akayev, in 
his speech, expressed his satisfaction for those who drafted the 
Constitution of the Kyrgyz Republic. It is obvious that this 
basic law opens the way for further enhancement of the social 
and economic development of the Republic. [words indistinct] 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

