<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prosecutor's Office Investigates High-Level Corruption </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prosecutor's Office Investigates High-Level Corruption </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405193294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1149 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0405193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 4 May (SNARK) -- Artavazd Gevorkyan, 
Armenian General Prosecutor, reported today to the Armenian 
temporary Parliamentary commission that presently the 
Prosecutor's Office is investigating seven criminal cases 
connected with the abuse of power by high rank officials. 
  The temporary Parliamentary commission is engaged in control 
of the corresponding inquest group of the Armenian Prosecutor's 
Office. 
  He said the inquest group has revealed "a system of theft 
and 
misappropriation of big money sums, coming to a person through a 
dummy." 
  The General Prosecutor declared that some persons, engaged 
in 
this case, had left Armenia, and it hampers the effective 
investigation. 
  He also reported that the Interior Ministry is intensively 
searching these persons. The General Prosecutor added that over 
1,000 people in Armenia are in a search on suspicion of 
committing various crimes. Mr. Gevorkyan said nobody has 
exerted any pressure on him connected with the cases of power 
abuse. 

</TEXT>

