<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Aliyev Visit to Belgium </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Aliyev Visit to Belgium </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Dehaene </H4>

<F P=102> NC0405184894 Baku TURAN in English 1547 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0405184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels (4 May) TURAN -- This morning in Brussels 
in the governmental residence, a meeting between Azerbaijan's 
President, Geydar Aliyev and Belgium's Prime Minister Jean Luc 
Dehaene took place. During their meeting they discussed issues 
of bilateral cooperation and regional security. Aliyev told the 
Prime Minister about the developments in the 
Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict. Both sides were unanimous in the 
opinion that the conflict should be solved by peaceful means. 
Azerbaijan's joining the preliminary document of the 
"Partnership for the Sake of Peace" programme will promote the 
development of Azeri-Belgian relations. 
  "We support the attempts to restore peace and stability in 
the Caucasus and support the negotiation process within the CSCE 
Minsk Group framework," said Dehaene. After the talks, Aliyev 
said that Belgium will review the draft for an agreement on 
friendship and cooperation plus a number of other agreements put 
forth by Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

