<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani Attack, Border Shelling Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azerbaijani Attack, Border Shelling Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505072994 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1700 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505072994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1700 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Armenian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani Army again intensified its 
aggressive operations along the northeastern border of Armenia 
on the morning of 3 May. The Armenian Defense Ministry press 
service reported that the enemy subjected the border settlements 
and defensive positions in Noyemberyanskiy, Idzhevanskiy, 
Tavushskiy, and Berd rayons to heavy artillery shelling as of 
1800. All types of weapons were used. 
  In an attempt to fulfill a recently planned military 
operation by the Azerbaijani Army command, a large armed group 
in Kazakhskiy Rayon launched an attack at 2100 with the support 
of tanks against Berdavan in Noyemberyanskiy Rayon. The enemy 
achieved some success against our border guards and approached 
the village. However, after 40 minutes, the Armenian Army 
fighters regrouped their forces and threw the enemy back and 
recovered their initial positions. The positional battles 
continued until 2400. Both sides suffered losses. 
  The Azerbaijani formations fiercely shelled Vazashen and 
Diran in Idzhevanskiy Rayon, Aygepar and Paravakar in Tavushskiy 
Rayon, and Vahan in Krasnoselskiy Rayon last night. Casualty 
figures are being determined. Our border guards took 
countermeasures and silenced the enemy at dawn. 
  According to the press service, a relative calm prevailed on 
Armenia's northeastern border during the day today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

