<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Heavy Fighting Reported in Terterskiy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405183394 Baku TURAN in English 1547 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0405183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (4 May) TURAN -- Heavy fightings, which began 
yesterday morning, continues, the head of Executive power of 
Terter city, Sardar Gamidov, told Turan at 1300. He said that 
on 3 May the Armenian troops resumed offensive towards the city 
of Terter from the village of Gyzyl-oba (Karmiravan). The 
Armenian Army is armed with artillery and military hardware and 
tries to break the defense of the Azeri Army. According to 
Gamidov, over the past two days the Armenian units lost many 
lives in this direction but failed to achieve success. At the 
same time, the Armenian troops try move further along the road 
Agdam-Barda. Fierce fighting are taking place in the village of 
Bash-Gervend. 
  The same source reports that last evening the Armenian 
troops 
shelled the city of Barda from Grad plants. Wounded and damages 
are reported. 
  According to unofficial sources, there is no fighting at 
another sections of the front. 

</TEXT>

