<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Interviewed on Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Interviewed on Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505094194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0855 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Dmitriy Gorokhov and </F>
Georgiy Shelenkov] 
  [Excerpts] Cairo, 5 May (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev has ended his visit to Egypt [passage 
omitted] 
  Before leaving Cairo A. Kozyrev gave an exclusive interview 
to an ITAR-TASS correspondent. "The agreement signed yesterday 
[between Israel and the PLO]," he said, "is a good start for the 
next stage of Middle East settlement. Equally strenuous work is 
ahead, that is, implementation of the signed document, which 
will raise many issues, for a new authority means new problems. 
But we will assist in this, too. 
  "We stressed very clearly our vital interest in this region 
which is close to us. Russia therefore will participate in the 
peace process in the future, too. We are already thinking about 
the next steps in further developing the Palestinian-Israeli 
settlement and in other areas. We will pay special attention to 
the Syrian aspect. 
  "Russia intends to develop in every possible way its 
bilateral relations with all the countries in the region, first 
of all with Egypt. Boris Yeltsin's message was received by 
President Mubarak warmly and with understanding. Now, without 
delay, we will start preparing for his forthcoming official 
visit to Moscow. 
  "Also, we will develop relations with Israel. Yesterday 
evening, after the signing, I had a meeting with [Israeli Prime 
Minister] Rabin which was geared toward strengthening our 
contacts established during the Israeli premier's recent visit 
to Moscow." 

</TEXT>

