<H3> <TI>   Visit by High-Level Tajik Delegation Previewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit by High-Level Tajik Delegation Previewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505062394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0612 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505062394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe May 5 TASS -- A delegation of the Tajik 
Government led by chairman of the Tajik parliament Emomali 
Rakhmonov is leaving for Moscow today, ITAR-TASS learned from 
the press service of the head of the Tajik Republic. 
  During the visit the Tajik delegation is expected to meet 
Russian top leaders to discuss a wide range of questions on 
deepening and expanding political, economic and military 
cooperation between the Russian Federation and Tajikistan. The 
sides are expected to discuss the merger of the Russian and 
Tajik monetary systems as well. 
  The Tajik delegation includes Chairman of the Tajik Council 
of Ministers Abdulmadjid Samadov, Chairman of the Tajik Central 
Bank Kayum Kavmidinov and a large group of experts. 
  Problems faced by the Russian-speaking population in 
Tajikistan and issues of reinforcing the state border with 
Afghanistan will be high on the agenda of the Moscow talks held 
in the framework of the visit to Russia by the Chairman of the 
Tajik parliament Emomali Rakhmonov which begins today, said 
Anatoliy Adamishin, Russian deputy foreign minister, on 
Wednesday. 
  During Rakhmonov's visit to Moscow the sides will discuss 
issues of Russo-Tajik economic cooperation and an internal 
political situation in Tajikistan and in partucular, prospects 
for a dialogue with the opposition. According to Adamishin, 
Russia has made considerable efforts to put out the flame of 
civil war in Tajikistan. The Russian diplomat welcomed the 
results of the first round of talks between Dushanbe and the 
opposition, and in particular, the fact acknowledged by the 
sides that a key to the solution of the problem is the political 
settlement of the situation in Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

