<H3> <TI>   Greek Foreign Minister Postpones Visit to Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greek Foreign Minister Postpones Visit to Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405153494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1409 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature] </F>
  [Text] The visit of the head of the Greek Foreign Ministry 
Karolas Papoulias to Moscow scheduled for May 3-5 "has been 
postponed for an indefinite term." The new date is to be 
coordinated via diplomatic channels, a top-ranking Russian 
diplomat in charge for Greece reported to Interfax. 
  He does not rule out that the contact between Russian 
Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev and Karolas Papoulias can take place in 
Cairo. 
  As it is known, on Tuesday Kozyrev came to Cairo, the 
Egyptian capital, to participate in signing of the agreement on 
Gaza Strip and Jericho between Israel and Palestine as a 
representative of the country-co-sponsor of the peaceful process 
in the Middle East. "As far as Papoulias is concerned, his 
presence in Cairo is also obligatory because at present Greece 
chairs the European Union," said Interfax interlocutor. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-61294 </DOCNO>
