<H3> <TI>   Deputy Defense Minister Meets ROK Counterpart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Defense Minister Meets ROK Counterpart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405203194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1519 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian First Deputy Defense Minister Andrey 
Kokoshin praised the results of his South Korean counterpart Yi 
Pyong-tae visit to Russia that ended Tuesday [3 May]. He told 
Interfax that the Republic of Korea was a very important partner 
for Russia in consolidating security in the Asian-Pacific region. 
  He said that Russia's relations with the Republic of Korea 
were a major factor helping Russia enter what he called the 
Asian-Pacific integration system. 
  The South Korean defense minister met with Kokoshin and 
Colonel General Mikhail Kolesnikov, chief of the General Staff, 
to discuss bilateral military political relations and 
cooperation in providing security in the region. 

</TEXT>

