<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Warns Against Materiel Transfer to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Warns Against Materiel Transfer to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405185494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1800 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As reported by the press service of the Defense 
Ministry, the Ukrainian Defense Ministry has come to know that 
the ferrying of over 20 Tu-22 missile-carrier combat aircraft to 
the Russian Federation is being made ready at two Black Sea 
Fleet aviation regiments. It is planned that the flight will be 
made against the background of regular tactical flight exercises 
of the Black Sea Fleet Air Force from the air bases of 
Oktyabrskoye and Veseloye in Crimea to the Russian military 
airfield in Krasnodarsk kray's Krymsk. 
  The press service of the Ukrainian Defense Ministry 
emphasizes that any attempts to transfer materiel and other 
Black Sea Fleet material wealth outside our state, are against 
the law and will inevitably lead to exacerbating the situation 
surrounding issues of dividing the Black Sea Fleet. 

</TEXT>

