<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Meets U.S. Security Council Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Prime Minister Meets U.S. Security Council Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405164194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1606 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UNKRINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 4 May, TASS -- Ukrainian Vice-Prime Minister 
Valeriy Shmarov met U.S. National Security Council Senior 
Director Nicholas Burns in Kiev on Wednesday [4 May] to discuss 
the implementation of the agreement signed by Russia, Ukraine 
and the United States to scrap Ukrainian strategic nuclear 
missiles. 
  Shmarov stressed that Ukraine has been observing its 
commitments under the agreement, adding that disarmament 
requires proper financial support. 
  Speaking about the safety of Ukrainian nuclear power plants, 
Shmarov said that Ukrainian experts are preparing proposals to 
this effect and will submit them to the upcoming G-7 summit 
meeting in Naples. 
  The Ukrainian vice-premier also informed the U.S. guest 
about conversion and space exploration programmes which offer 
good opportunities for cooperation with American businesses. 
  The meeting was attended by U.S. Ambassador to Ukraine 
William Green Miller. 

</TEXT>

