<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk on Hopes for Parliamentary Approval of Accords </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk on Hopes for Parliamentary Approval of Accords </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405155994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1503 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk, meeting on 
Wednesday the head of a delegation of U.S. economists, Nicholas 
Burns, expressed the hope that Ukraine's newly-elected 
parliament would ratify the Ukrainian-American agreements signed 
during his January visit to the United States. 
  The American economists have come to Ukraine, where they are 
due to stay till 6 May, to find out how the country could use 
the economic aid to a sum of $350 million the United States 
plans to give it. According to Kravchuk, America is going to 
help Ukraine reform its economy, make investments in it and step 
up trade with the country. 
  Following his meeting with Kravchuk, Burns said a 
Ukrainian-U.S. fund was due to be set up this summer to give 
loans to private Ukrainian businesses. 

</TEXT>

