<H3> <TI>   Mitterrand Advises Sticking to Course With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mitterrand Advises Sticking to Course With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505110594 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1700 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry's press service informed 
Estonian Radio that Prime Minister Mart Laar, who is currently 
in France on a working visit, met with President Francois 
Mitterrand today. Their meeting, which proceeded in a friendly 
atmosphere, dealt mostly with Estonian-Russian relations and 
issues to do with the Russian troop withdrawal. The following 
recommendation by Francois Mitterrand made its mark: Be patient 
at the negotiations while sticking firmly to your positions. 
  The French Foreign Ministry gave a dinner in honor of Mart 
Laar at which Minister of State Pierre Mehaignerie made a 
speech. He highlighted the speed and fruitfulness of Estonian 
economic reforms and stated that France will in every way 
support Estonia's advances toward the European Union. The 
minister emphasized that the European Union must be open by the 
end of the century to all those who form a part of European 
history and culture. 

</TEXT>

