<H3> <TI>   Border Guard, Russian Attache Agree on Kurdish Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Guard, Russian Attache Agree on Kurdish Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0505090294 Tallinn BNS in English 1800 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0505090294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Tallinn, May 04, BNS -- The head of the Estonian 
Border Guard Department and the Russian embassy's military 
attache in Tallinn at a private meeting this week decided that 
the border- related departments of both countries will 
themselves try to find out who is responsible for letting 
illegal Kurdish immigrants across the border and whether Russia 
should take back the Kurds. 
  The departments in Estonia and Russia must resolve the issue 
of the Kurds without creating a strife between themselves or 
interference by the world community, Tarmo Kouts, the head of 
the Estonian border department said. 
  Kouts at the meeting requested from Russian Military Attache 
Anatoli Tschizhikov that Russia answer to letters by the 
Estonian department concerning the Kurds' illegal crossing of 
the border. 
  Kouts told BNS he hopes to get an answer by Friday [6 May]. 
  "From that answer we will be able to conclude whether the 
issue can be settled at our departments' level or has to be 
referred to the Foreign Ministry and the broader public." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

