<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Official Denies Reports of Coup Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministry Official Denies Reports of Coup Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0405141994 Tallinn ETA in English 0753 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0405141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From 4 May PEVALEHT, p.3; "News Bulletin" No. 85/94] </F>
  [Text] An Interior Ministry official denied the reports of 
a coup plan prepared by Russian officers, announced by MP Mart 
Niklus at a picket at the Russian naval HQ on Monday [2 May]. 
Niklus had declared that a secret meeting of Russian officers 
took place in Tartu on April 23 where an armed coup was 
discussed. He further claimed that the conspirators are armed 
and have cells in different regions of Estonia. 
  The PEVALEHT reports that a dismissed Defence League member 
had sent a letter recently to President Lennart Meri and 
Commander in Chief General Aleksander Einseln, claiming that 
retired Russian officers had been preparing a coup at the 
aforementioned date. The man had added that some servicemen of 
the Estonia Defence Forces have been involved in the preparation. 
  An unnamed Interior Ministry official dismissed the report, 
explaining that April 23 had been the day of the payment of 
pensions to the retired Russian military and their possible 
expressions of dissatisfaction can hardly be qualified as a 
preparation of coup attempt. 

</TEXT>

