<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Adopts Law on Port Use, Management, Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Adopts Law on Port Use, Management, Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0505092794 Tallinn BNS in English 1515 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0505092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, May 04, BNS -- The Latvian Cabinet accepted 
Tuesday [3 May] a law on ports providing for the use, management 
and security of ports, Communication Minister Andris Gutmanis 
said at a press conference. 
  The law is urgent in the present situation of growing 
competition between Baltic sea ports because it will help to 
improve the main legislative drawbacks concerning national and 
municipal port ownership, Gutmanis said. 
  The planned revenue from port operation in 1994 is 15.5 
million lats from which 1.1 million lats will be transferred to 
local budgets to develop port territory infrastructures. 
  Under the law, port duties are covered by owners of cargo. 

</TEXT>

