BFN 

  [Text] Riga, May 04, BNS -- As many as 102,222 Latvian 
residents, or 6.6 percent of the country's economically active 
population, were looking for job on May 3, according to 
operative figures from the State Employment Service. 
  From those, 88,136 have registered themselves as unemployed, 
36,016 receive allowances, 31,443 have been seeking jobs for 
more than six months. 
  In March, the joblessness rate was 6.5 percent, the service 
