<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders Hold Talks on Nagorno-Karabakh in Bishkek </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders Hold Talks on Nagorno-Karabakh in Bishkek </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Akayev Addresses Meeting </H4>

<F P=102> LD0405165194 Bishkek KYRGYZKABAR in Russian 1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek KYRGYZKABAR </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bishkek, 4 May -- A meeting on settling the 
Armenian-Azerbaijan conflict in Nagorno-Karabakh opened today at 
Kyrgyzstan's government house. President Askar Akayev addressed 
those present: 
  The Karabakh conflict is a complex knot of problems that has 
centuries old traditions. Generations of people of the two 
fraternal republics should not be victims of historic mistakes 
and contradictions. It is our belief that these problems should 
be solved today on the basis of present day realities, on the 
principles of tolerance and mutual concessions. The fact that 
the Karabakh problem is being discussed within the framework of 
the CIS Interparliamentary Assembly, which is led by the 
Vladimir Shumeyko, allows us to believe that Legislative 
Branches of power will find a safe mechanism for putting out the 
flame of the fraternal war. There are no winners in this war. 
Your efforts aimed at peaceful settlment of the Karabakh 
conflict will be appreciated by future generations and by 
history. I wish you success in your job, peace and well being 
to your people. 
  [Signed] President Askar Akayev. 

</TEXT>

