<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   No. Ossetian Leader on Ingushetia Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No. Ossetian Leader on Ingushetia Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405131794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1254 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz May 4 TASS -- "The provisions of the 
social concord agreement, signed in the Kremlin on April 28, 
must serve as guidelines for talks between the presidents and 
official delegations of North Ossetia and Ingushetia," North 
Ossetian President Akhsarbek Galazov said here today, addressing 
leaders of North Ossetian art unions, rectors of higher 
educational establishments, and representatives of the 
republic's national cultural centres. 
  The North Ossetian leader went on record for the 
continuation 
of the dialogue with the Ingush side, but bluntly rejected the 
idea of a moratorium on border changes. In his opinion, it is 
necessary to completely delete from the agenda the question of 
recarving the borders of the North Caucasian area, because this 
may provoke a new tragedy in the region. 
  The North Ossetian president dwelt at length on the 
forthcoming celebration of the 220th anniversary of Ossetia's 
accession to Russia and the 210th anniversary of the foundation 
of the city of Vladikavkaz. The jubilee celebrations, devoted 
to these dates, will be held from October 7 to October 15. 
Galazov said that these dates "have not lost their importance 
at all, but are assuming a new historical meaning in the light 
of modern political problems". 

</TEXT>

