<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Laar Confers With French Leaders in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Laar Confers With French Leaders in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0505090094 Tallinn ETA in English 1712 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0505090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Estonian Prime Minister Mart Laar, currently on a 
visit to France, was received, on Wednesday [4 May], by French 
President Francois Mitterand, Estonian Foreign Ministry press 
service told ETA. 
  At the meeting, primarily Estonian-Russian relations and 
issues connected to Russian troop withdrawal from Estonia were 
discussed. "Be patient, but remain firm of your positions," 
Mitterand said. 
  A festive dinner was given in honour of Laar at the French 
Foreign Ministry, where French state minister Pierre Mehaignerie 
held a speech, in which he pointed at the success of Estonian 
economic reforms and confirmed that France supported Estonia's 
moving towards European Union. "European Union has to open its 
doors to all those that are a part of European history and 
culture by the end of the century," Mehaignerie stressed. 
  Mart Laar was also received by French Prime Minister Edouard 
Balladur and Foreign Minister Alain Juppe. Laar is to return to 
Estonia on Thursday. 

</TEXT>

