<H3> <TI>   Russia To Continue Disaster Aid to Kyrgyzstan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia To Continue Disaster Aid to Kyrgyzstan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405104894 Moscow RIA in English 0846 GMT 4 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0405104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bishkek, May 4, RIA -- Russia will continue aiding 
Kyrgyzstan in its effort to make up for the harm done by natural 
disasters -- earth tremors and avalanches -- which are so 
frequent in that mountainous republic, said Vladimir Shumeyko, 
who chairs the Federation Council of Russia's Federal Assembly, 
now on an official visit in Bishkek. Kyrgyzstan is the site for 
a field staff of the Russian Ministry for Emergency Situations, 
which runs programmes of measures to prevent natural disasters, 
forecast them and provide early warning of tremors and 
avalanches. 
  The town of Uzgen is where a number of prefab houses, 
purchased in Russia with Russian easy-term credits, have been 
built to give shelter to victims of natural disasters. Kyrgyz 
President Askar Akayev estimates that last year Russia's aid 
helped save over 14,000 of the republic's citizens. 

</TEXT>

