<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Russia International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Meets Slovak Counterpart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Prime Minister Meets Slovak Counterpart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904173394 Moscow RIA in English 1510 GMT 29 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2904173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 29, RIA -- Yuriy Yarov and Brigita 
Smengerova, vice-premiers of Russia and Slovakia and 
co-presidents of the Intergovernment Commission for Trade, 
Economic, Research and Technological Cooperation, met in Moscow 
today to discuss payment prospects for Soviet and Russian debts 
to Slovakia, Russian oil deliveries and nuclear research and 
industrial cooperation. 
  The conferees exchanged opinions on the political and 
economic situation and specified both countries' stances on 
bilateral trade and economic cooperation. They also discussed 
organisational matters for the nearest session of the 
intergovernment commission, due in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

