<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Russia International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Claims DPRK Incapable of Producing Nukes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Claims DPRK Incapable of Producing Nukes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1804060894 Tokyo TOKYO SHIMBUN in Japanese 17 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 5--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1804060894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo TOKYO SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 16 Apr, JIJI -- Russian Vice Foreign 
Minister Panov (in charge of Asian Affairs) gave an interview to 
the JIJI NEWS AGENCY on 16 April. Touching on the military 
alliance included in the treaty of goodwill and mutual 
assistance which the former Soviet Union had signed with the 
DPRK (North Korea), Panov stated: "It will be reviewed taking 
various factors into consideration." He also disclosed that the 
treaty will be revised before its expiration in 1996. 
  In the interview, Vice Minister Panov stated: "North Korea 
does not have the technology for developing nuclear weapons." 
Panov stressed that North Korea's nuclear arms development 
issue should be resolved not by compulsory measures such as 
economic sanctions, but by peaceful measures such as the 
convocation of an international conference advocated by Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

