<F P=101> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gorbachev Wary of PFP, Expects New European Split </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gorbachev Wary of PFP, Expects New European Split </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504163094 Moscow RIA in English 1339 GMT 25 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2504163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] St. Petersburg, April 25, RIA -- Mikhail Gorbachev 
is "extremely critical" of the NATO Partnership for Peace 
programme, he said to the press on his two-day business visit to 
this city. 
  "European political processes are too dynamic and 
sophisticated to be understood and influenced even with UN help. 
It's good that the Duma is debating the situation round the 
NATO programme. Russia can't afford to stay aloof to Poland's 
and other neighbour countries' NATO membership." 
  The ex-president of the ex-USSR doesn't think the European 
destiny can be determined with the help of a former cold war 
tool -- or Europe will be in for a new split. 

</TEXT>

