<H3> <TI>   President To Resign if Opposition Constitution Adopted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President To Resign if Opposition Constitution Adopted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504150994 Moscow RIA in English 1339 GMT 25 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2504150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, April 25, RIA -- The existing power shall 
not, and will not be deposed by violence, President 
Ter-Petrosyan said to parliament today to propose a provisional 
arrangement before the new constitution is passed. According to 
it, parliament shall offer for referendum, without preliminary 
debates, either of the two constitutional drafts or both--the 
official version from the president-headed Constitutional 
Commission, and six opposition parties' alternative draft. 
  If the latter is adopted, the president will immediately 
resign. If his variant passes, Armenia will need new 
presidential and parliamentary elections, holds Mr. 
Ter-Petrosyan. He also deems it necessary for parliament to 
pass the citizenship and election bills within the current 
session, reports SNARK news agency. 

</TEXT>

