<H3> <TI>   RMK Foreign Minister Views CSCE Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RMK Foreign Minister Views CSCE Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2304120194 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0846 GMT 23 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> NC2304120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert ("Golos Armenii" daily), 04/23/94 -- RMK 
[Republic of Mountainous Karabakh] Minister of Foreign Affairs 
Arkadiy Gukasyan held a briefing yesterday, dedicated to the 
CSCE Minsk Group meeting in Prague on April 11-15. The Minister 
also spoke on the reasons why the meeting between the Armenian, 
Azeri and RMK representatives, planned to be held in Moscow on 
April 15, failed. According to Mr. Gukasyan, Azerbaijan caused 
the failure, by not accepting the Russian cease fire initiative. 
  A. Gukasyan positively evaluated Jan Eliasson's work and 
stressed that the new CSCE Chairman realistically estimates the 
opportunities and demonstrates a constructive approach to 
resolution of the Karabakh problem. If he continues working in 
a similar manner, concrete results will be possible soon. 
  The Minister stressed the importance of documents on 
increasing trust between the conflicting sides, prepared in 
Prague. The document will be signed by the CSCE High Officials 
Committee. A plan on the initial stage of introducing CSCE 
observer mission was also coordinated during the meeting in 
Prague. 
  Mr. Gukasyan stressed once again the importance of 
coordinating the Russian, CSCE and UN peace initiatives. 

</TEXT>

