<H3> <TI>   Presidential Spokesman Views Cease-Fire Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidential Spokesman Views Cease-Fire Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904140194 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0709 GMT 29 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> NC2904140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("Lragir" daily), 04/29/94 -- Presidential 
spokesman Levon Zurabyan held a briefing and particularly 
touched the answer of the RMK [Republic of Mountainous Karabakh] 
authorities on the Azeri cease fire proposal. 
  The message by the RMK authorities confirmed a cease fire 
agreement, starting 0:01am on April 29, on conditions stipulated 
by the Moscow agreement of February 18. 
  Mr. Zurabyan noted that the Azeri proposal was for a short 
term (10 days) cease fire, which would be used to "take a 
breath" in order to restart the military operations with new 
force. At the same time, the Azeri side takes no obligations by 
this cease fire, which is naturally not acceptable for 
Mountainous Karabakh. 
  It was stressed that Mountainous Karabakh will establish a 
cease fire only in case, all topics of the above mentioned 
agreement are met. 
  "Armenia completely agrees with the position of Mountainous 
Karabakh", Zurabyan said. 

</TEXT>

