<H3> <TI>   Lezghins Reportedly Fighting in Karabakh Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lezghins Reportedly Fighting in Karabakh Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405135194 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0704 GMT 4 May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> NC0405135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("LRAGIR", "AZG" dailies), 05/04/94 -- The 
Azerbaijani mass media spread information on April 30, telling 
that Lezghin soldiers are fighting in the Karabakh Army. The 
RMK [Republic of Mountainous Karabakh] defense army headquarters 
confirmed this information, noting that indeed, 23 Lezghin 
volunteers have recently arrived to Stepanakert from Khachmach 
and Khudat districts at the north of Azerbaijan, and expressed a 
desire to fight against the Azerbaijani army. 
  The commander of the Lezghin group Hajibek said, not only 
the fortune of Armenians but also Lezghins, Talyshs and other 
national minorities, whose historical lands were joined to 
Azerbaijan by Stalin's order, is now being solved in Karabakh. 

</TEXT>

