  [Text] According to our special correspondent in Chisinau, 
Belarusian Supreme Soviet Chairman Mechyslaw Hryb and Prime 
Minister Vyacheslaw Kebich have today begun a visit to Moldova. 
The Belarusian parliament speaker and the Cabinet of Ministers 
chairman went to Moldova at the invitation of that country's 
leaders. Strengthening and developing economic and cultural ties 
between the two republics is the main goal of the visit to 
Chisinau by Mechyslaw Hryb and Vyacheslaw Kebich. 
  In the morning, the delegation met with Moldovan President 
Mircea Snegur, signed documents on bilateral cooperation, and 
held a news conference with journalists. At the news 
conference, the Belarusian and Moldovan leaders emphasized that 
such cooperation is in the interests of both states and people. 
The visit by Mechyslaw Hryb and Vyacheslaw Kebich will last two 
days. 

