<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Volskiy on Social Accord Treaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Volskiy on Social Accord Treaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505164594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1429 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Lyudmila Aleksandrova and </F>
Lyudmila Yermakova] 
  [Text] Moscow May 5 TASS -- "We, representatives of 
business circles, expect much of the treaty", President of the 
Russian Union of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs Arkadiy 
Volskiy said in interview with TASS on Thursday. 
  This view is shared by other participants in today's second- 
stage signing ceremony in the Kremlin, during which Russia's 
major industrialists, agrarians, entrepreneurs and bankers put 
their signatures under the treaty on social accord. 
  The main thing that prompted the Russian Union of 
Industrialists and Entrepreneurs to sign the document is 
renunciation of the use of force and any actions involving 
bloodshed, Volskiy added. He noted that so far the point at 
issue has been accord in the political sphere, but this is not 
enough for the economy. The next thing to do is to work out 
appropriate measures with a view to stop the current economic 
recession and output decline, the industrialist believes. 
"Unless we manage to pass this stage, unless we achieve 
economic accord, the treaty will become senseless", he stressed. 
  Presidential Aide Georgiy Satarov told reporters that the 
country's business community had been amply represented at 
today's signing ceremony. Their role is especially significant 
now that the crisis is being aggravated, and they may become the 
principal force to help overcome this crisis, the aide 
emphasised. He reported that the next stage of the signing 
would take place on May 12. This will not be the last stage, 
since the document is open for further signing by any 
organization concerned and interested. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

