<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Party Urges Yeltsin `To Restore Justice' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Party Urges Yeltsin `To Restore Justice' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505124094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1122 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 5 TASS -- The high council of the Liberal 
Democratic Party (LDP) led by Vladimir Zhirinovskiy sent an open 
letter to the Russian president in which it grieves over the 
party's woes, calling for "urgent measures to restore justice." 
  The letter circulated today highlights the party's 
achievements and in particular, the fact that the majority of 
citizens had voted for the Constitution only thanks to active 
support given to the Constitution by the LDP. The letter 
contains complaints over the fact that "the LDP leader Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy had not been given the right to form a new 
government and was not even received by the president after the 
elections." 
  Among other things, the LDP high council complains that the 
leader of the victorious party was not admitted to the mass 
media, that there is not a single minister from the LDP in the 
government and that "both the party and its leader are being 
outrageously attacked and unscrupulously slandered." 
  The LDP leadership expressed "surprise" at an interview 
given 
by Boris Yeltsin to the FIGARO newspaper in which Yeltsin 
"indirectly accused the party and its leaders of advocating 
fascism." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

