<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov Rejects Conclusions of Expert Team on Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov Rejects Conclusions of Expert Team on Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605092694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0910 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0605092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 6 TASS -- The conclusions of Aleksandr 
Sobyanin's expert team on the results of the elections to the 
Russian Parliament and of the December 12 referendum "smack of 
an outright provocation", ITAR-TASS was told by Sergey Filatov, 
chief of the presidential administration. 
  Commenting today on the article published by the newspaper 
IZVESTIYA, which claims that the "results of the elections and 
the referendum were rigged", Filatov said that the conclusions 
of the team "play into the hands of the irreconcilable 
opposition" at the time when the social concord agreement is 
being signed. 
  As to the team itself, which the newspaper claims to be "a 
team under the presidential administration", it is pertinent to 
note that it "has nothing to do with the administration", 
Filatov said. 
  "There is a team headed by Sobyanin, which used to analyse 
the results of the elections, the voting in the supreme soviet, 
etc., from the very first Congress of People's Deputies," 
Filatov stated. "Later, those people went into science," he 
added. The head of the presidential administration said that he 
was "most doubtful" about the methods they are using in their 
calculations. 
  Filatov said that a denial of the article was drawn up and 
would be handed over for publication to the newspaper IZVESTIYA. 

</TEXT>

