<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Notes State Debts to Army Growing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Notes State Debts to Army Growing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505195794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1805 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting of the commission for financial issues of 
the Russian armed forces presided over by First Deputy Defense 
Minister Andrey Kokoshin Thursday focused on the results of 
financing the army over the first four months of this year and 
the spending of particular units and districts. 
  Salaries of officers and civilian personnel, food, nuclear 
security and combat training were among the priorities. It was 
pointed out that the withdrawal of Russian troops and their 
accommodation required an unprecedented amount of money. 
  As for the funds set aside from military appropriations to 
pay for the state defense orders, they were used mainly to pay 
for the production of combat management and communications 
hardware, high- precision weapons and radio and electronic 
counteraction means. 
  According to a Defense Ministry statement, the meeting was 
told that financing the army activities involved long delays, 
while the state's debt to the army and the defense industries 
continued to grow. 

</TEXT>

