<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fire Rages at Beloyarsk Nuclear Power Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fire Rages at Beloyarsk Nuclear Power Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605110194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0952 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0605110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Karlov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 6 May (ITAR-TASS) -- The fire which broke 
out at Beloyarsk nuclear power station (Sverdlovsk oblast in the 
Urals) at 0924 at the third power unit of Beloyarsk AES was 
still not extinguished by 1300 today. The ITAR-TASS 
correspondent was informed of this in the Information and Public 
Relations Directorate of the Ministry of Atomic Energy of the 
Russian Federation. 
  In the opinion of specialists, the workforce, population, 
and 
environment are not being affected by radiation. The accident 
has been given a preliminary assessment of level one on the 
international scale of nuclear incidents (the levels are graded 
one to seven -- Chernobyl was grade seven). 
  The fire broke out during repair work on the third power 
unit 
which has been under repair since 23 April. There was a leak of 
non-radioactive sodium from the drainage of the secondary 
circuit in one of the machine rooms. The sodium ignited. 
Efforts to extinguish the fire are continuing. 

</TEXT>

