<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Privatization of Energiya Rocket, Space Firm Approved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Privatization of Energiya Rocket, Space Firm Approved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605104194 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
0630 GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0605104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Authorization has been given for the flotation of 
one of the largest Russian rocket and space firms, the Energiya 
research and production association [RPA] named after Korolev. 
In pursuance of a government decision, the Energiya rocket and 
space corporation named after Korolev is being created from the 
Energiya RPA and its subsidiary in the town of Primorsk in 
Leningrad Oblast in the form of an open joint-stock company. 
  Fifty-one percent of the ordinary shares, amounting to 38 
percent of the total number of shares issued by the corporation, 
have been assigned to the federal authorities. Ten percent of 
the total number of shares are set aside for purchase by the 
corporation's work force. In accordance with a stipulation from 
the State Committee for the Management of State Property 
[Goskomimushchestvo], the organization of a sale of 12 percent 
of the corporation's shares at a closed check auction is being 
changed. 
  The Energiya corporation's articles of association should be 
presented to the Russian Government within a month. Yuriy 
Semenov, general director of the Energiya RPA, has been 
appointed president of the corporation until the first 
shareholders' meeting. 

</TEXT>

