<H3> <TI>   Duma Supports Black Sea Economic Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Supports Black Sea Economic Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505214394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1941 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505214394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 5 TASS--Russian State Duma deputies 
attach great importance to the activities of the Parliamentary 
Assembly for the Black Sea Economic Cooperation, Valentin 
Kovalyov, deputy chairman of the State Duma and head of the 
Russian delegation participating in the parliamentary assembly, 
told a news conference on Thursday. 
  The news conference was devoted to the results of the work 
of 
the committee for culture, education and social activities of 
the parliamentary assembly. 
  This is the form of the parliamentary integration, Valentin 
Kovalyov stressed, which has prospects for the development of 
friendly relations between countries of the Black Sea basin, a 
spokesman for press service of the State Duma of the Federal 
Assembly of the Russian Federation told ITAR-TASS. 
  The participants of the news conference urged to speed up 
the 
ratification of the convention on cooperation in the field of 
culture, education, science and information. 
  In addition, the committee of the parliamentary assembly for 
the Black Sea economic cooperation plans to resolve the problem 
of the mutual recognition of diplomas and scientific degrees in 
member countries, organize more often creative meetings, book 
fairs, and widen and maintain contacts in the field of culture 
and education. 
  Representatives of the committee told journalists that a 
resolution was adopted on Wednesday which proposed to give a new 
impetus to the program for historical study of the Black Sea 
basin. 

