<H3> <TI>   Travkin May Represent Government in State Duma </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Travkin May Represent Government in State Duma </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK0505100094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 May 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK0505100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [NEGA report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Nikolay </F>
Travkin's New Appointment"] 
  [Text] According to trustworthy information, the question 
of appointing Nikolay Travkin, leader of the Democratic Party of 
Russia, as Russian Government representative in the State Duma 
is now being decided. In this connection Nikolay Travkin 
obviously would have to retire as chairman of the Democratic 
party faction in the lower house of the Federal Assembly. 

</TEXT>

