<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Stepashin: Chechnya Must Be Seen as Part of Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Stepashin: Chechnya Must Be Seen as Part of Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605094294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0605094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting between Boris Yeltsin and Dzhokhar Dudayev 
can take place only on condition that the Chechen leader 
recognizes that his republic is a part of the Russian 
Federation. Sergey Stepashin, director of the Russian Federal 
Counterintelligence Service, said this at a meeting on Thursday 
evening with members of the parliament and government of 
Kabarda-Balkaria in Nalchik. He expressed the view that Viktor 
Chernomyrdin is most likely to hold a dialogue with the Chechen 
leader since economic talks are the main way of resolving 
relations between Moscow and Groznyy. 
  Regarding the situation in the northern Caucasus, the 
director of the Federal Counterintelligence Service noted that 
one cannot speak of stabilization in the region without a 
settlement of relations with Chechnya. Stepashin said that, in 
its present form this republic represents a threat to the 
stability of the Russian Federation. In the view of the head of 
Russian counterintelligence, dialogue with Dudayev should be 
conducted in a tough manner and the primary task is 
normalization of the situation on the railroads crossing 
Chechnya. 

</TEXT>

