<F P=104>  Kiev UT-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk received 
Sir Leon Brittan, vice president of the European Union 
Commission and commissar for external economic affairs of the 
European Commissions, who is on a visit to our country at the 
invitation of the foreign affairs minister to familiarize 
himself with the situation in Ukraine and to find out about the 
course of reforms. A conversation took place in the course of 
which a wide variety of issues relating to cooperation between 
Ukraine and the EEC was raised. Ukraine attaches significant 
importance to the development of cooperation with the European 
Union, said President Kravchuk. We seek to have good relations 
with every country on the continent. 
  I am happy that work on preparation for the signing of an 
agreement between Ukraine and the EEC on partnership and 
cooperation is over. This cooperation will be on the basis of 
temporary accords. 
  President Kravchuk expressed the wish that the agreement 
should be signed as early as the beginning of June. This, he 
said, is necessitated by our economic and political problems. 

