<H3> <TI>   EU Announces Aid Package To Help Close Chernobyl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Announces Aid Package To Help Close Chernobyl </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505195994 Kiev UT-1 Television Network in Ukrainian 1600 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505195994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UT-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The European Union [EU] agrees to provide financial 
assistance to build two new reactors in Ukraine, on one 
condition, however: that all of the Chernobyl nuclear electric 
power station's generating sets are closed down. This was a 
statement made at a news conference in Strasbourg, held by five 
of the European Parliament's most influential party groupings 
that united in a campaign for the Chernobyl nuclear power 
station to close down. It was announced that 100 million ECU 
[European currency unit] would be allocated by the EURATOM 
[European Atomic Energy Community] organization. Some of the 
money will be provided from the TACIS [Technical Aid to the 
Commonwealth of Independent States] program and by the European 
Bank for Reconstruction and Development. Members of the European 
Parliament stressed that the G-7 member states would make a 
considerable contribution. 

</TEXT>

