<H3> <TI>   Crimean Government Building Evacuated Due to Bomb Threat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Government Building Evacuated Due to Bomb Threat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505105194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1018 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Leb Ryabchikov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol 5 May TASS -- The government of the 
Crimea received a bomb threat on Thursday [5 May] and the staff 
have been urgently evacuated from the building. 
  An unknown person called the policeman on duty at the 
government offices in the morning and said the building had been 
mined. 
  All employees were immediately evacuated and the building is 
being searched by special police units. 

</TEXT>

