<H3> <TI>   No Bomb Found </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Bomb Found </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505192594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1831 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Lev Ryabchikov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol 5 May TASS--No mine has been found in the 
building of the Crimean local government. 
  By 0200 on Thursday [5 May] afternoon, field engineers of 
the 
Black Sea Fleet's 126th Coastal Guard Division completed 
inspection of the building but failed to detect the reported 
explosive device. 
  The inspection was prompted by a telephone call this 
morning. 
An unidentified person said a mine had been planted in the 
government building, after which a government session was broken 
off and everybody was evacuated from the building. 

</TEXT>

