<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   To Meet Crimea's President Meshkov </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    To Meet Crimea's President Meshkov </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505164294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1516 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 5 May TASS--"Relations between Ukraine and 
Crimea should be built on an equal and mutually beneficial 
basis. This will be the main topic of my meeting with President 
Yuriy Meshkov, which is due to be held in Simferopol on 7 May," 
Ukrainian Acting Prime Minister Yefim Zvyahilskyy told TASS on 
Thursday [5 May]. 
  The proposed meeting is prompted by yesterday's closed-door 
talks between Zvyahilskyy and Crimea's Deputy Prime Minister 
Yevgeniy Saburov. The Ukrainian acting prime minister was 
pleased that when asked with whom the peninsula was siding, 
Saburov answered definitely: "with Ukraine." 
  "Only after this, I made up my mind to meet the Crimean 
president," Zvyahilskyy stressed. 

</TEXT>

