BFN 

  [Text] A state delegation from Tajikistan headed by Emomali 
Rakhmonov, head of state and chairman of the Tajikistan Supreme 
Soviet, left for Moscow today on a working visit at the 
invitation of Boris Yeltsin, president of Russian Federation. 
  The delegation comprises Abdujalil Samadov, chairman of the 
republic's Council of Ministers; Kayum Kavmiddinov, chairman of 
the National Bank; Rashid Olimov, minister of foreign Affairs; 
Rustam Mirzoyev, minister of economics and forecasting; 
(Yunusov), minister of finance; and a group of experts. 
  In Moscow Emomali Rakhmonov, head of state and chairman of 
the Tajikistan Supreme Soviet, will meet with Boris Yeltsin, 
president of the Russian Federation, and other state officials 
and will sign documents regulating mutual beneficial relations. 
  The state delegation was seen off at Dushanbe airport by the 
vice chairmen of the Supreme Soviet and of the Council of 
Ministers and other officials. 

