<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidents Niyazov, Nazarbayev Hold Phone Conversation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidents Niyazov, Nazarbayev Hold Phone Conversation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505170294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1624 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Kurbanova] </F>
  [Text] Ashgabat 5 May TASS -- President Saparmurad Niyazov 
of Turkmenistan and Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev had a 
telephone conversation on Wednesday [4 May] night, the 
"TURKMENSKAYA ISKRA" daily writes on Thursday. 
  The two leaders agreed to hold as soon as possible a meeting 
between heads of the Caspian countries to discuss various 
regional issues. 
  President Nazarbayev confirmed that Kazakhstan intended to 
participate in an international consortium, which would build 
gas and oil pipelines from Turkmenistan to the countries of 
Persian Gulf. 
  The two presidents also discussed ways of developing 
bilateral interstate relations on the basis of mutual benefit. 

</TEXT>

