<H3> <TI>   Armenian Attacks in Karabakh Said Repulsed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Attacks in Karabakh Said Repulsed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505181794 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Defense Ministry press service, 
Armenia's Armed Forces launched a new large scale offensive on 
the northern and northeastern sectors of the front at 0600 this 
morning. The Azerbaijani Army inflicted heavy losses on the 
enemy in Geranboy [Shaumyanovskiy] and Agdamskiy Rayons and 
forced them to retreat to their initial positions. 
  Supported by armored cars, the infantry units of the 
Armenian 
Army launched an attack on Kirmizikend [Karmiravan] in 
Terterskiy Rayon. Fighting continues in this region. 
  The desertions from the Armenian Army fighting in Karabakh 
has assumed a massive dimension. Colonel Grigoryan, commander 
of one of the military units of the Armenian Army fighting in 
Geranboy, shot and killed three Armenian soldiers from Gyumri 
for refusing to fight. 

</TEXT>

