<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Fire on CSCE Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Forces Fire on CSCE Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1162C Baku ZERKALO in Russian 30 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1162C </F>
<F P=104>  Baku ZERKALO </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article under the heading "Panorama": "Armed </F>
Forces of Armenia Fired on CSCE Mission"] 
  [Text] On 28 April a delegation of the CSCE [Conference on 
Security and Cooperation in Europe] Minsk Group was fired on by 
the Armenian armed forces in Azerbaijan's Terterskiy Rayon. The 
KHABAR-SERVICE agency learned about this from the UN government 
[as published] in Azerbaijan. By a stroke of luck there were no 
casualties among the members of the delegation. As Minister of 
Foreign Affairs of Azerbaijan Hasan Hasanov told a correspondent 
of the KHABAR-SERVICE agency, this happened despite the fact 
that while visiting Yerevan the leader of the delegation, Mr. 
Mathias Mosberg, a deputy of the Minsk Conference [as 
published], informed the leadership of Armenia about a 
forthcoming visit of the mission he heads to Azerbaijan's 
Terterskiy Rayon, which is located in the immediate proximity of 
the front line. It should be stressed that the delegation was in 
the region on a peace-making mission, and the belligerent 
parties had been informed about the future route to be traveled 
by foreign diplomats several days in advance of their arrival. 
After firing on the motorcade of Vladimir Kazimirov, ambassador 
at large of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, this 
winter, the armed forces of Armenia have in this manner now 
expressed their attitude toward the peacemaking efforts of 
intermediaries for the second time. 

</TEXT>

