<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Production Levels Decline </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Production Levels Decline </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1162E Baku ZERKALO in Russian 30 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1162E </F>
<F P=104>  Baku ZERKALO </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the heading "Panorama": "Oil </F>
Output Level Drops"] 
  [Text] The volume of oil production at the oil fields 
worked in the Republic has dropped annually by approximately 1 
million tonnes. A correspondent of the KHABAR-SERVICE agency 
learned this from sources in the State Oil Company of 
Azerbaijan. At present annual output stands at the level of 10 
million tonnes a year. This is largely due to the absence of 
necessary production technologies, because those available allow 
for extracting only 65 percent of producible oil. Lack of funds 
for repairs and the technical servicing of drilling rigs is 
another reason. In conjunction with this, about 2,000 wells both 
on land and at sea are completely idle at present. 

</TEXT>

