<H3> <TI>   Political Opposition More `Civilized' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Opposition More `Civilized' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1162B Baku ZERKALO in Russian 30 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1162B </F>
<F P=104>  Baku ZERKALO </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article under the heading "Panorama": "The </F>
Azerbaijani Opposition Has Become More Reasonable"] 
  [Text] As Leyla Yunusova, chairman of the Independent 
Democratic Party of Azerbaijan (NDPA), stated to the ANS-PRESS 
agency, compared to the previous periods the Azerbaijan 
opposition has sufficiently matured and become more civilized 
and restrained. In the words of Leyla Yunusova, no attempts to 
destabilize the situation in the Republic are being made by the 
opposition. On the contrary, the opposition is trying to engage 
in political struggle by more civilized and democratic methods. 
According to the NDPA chairman, three main political blocs have 
emerged in Azerbaijan: two oppositional blocs -- the Democratic 
Congress and the Centrist Parties Bloc -- and the third bloc -- 
the leadership of the country. As Leyla Yunusova stressed, there 
are also parties which for one reason or another do not 
subscribe to the points of view of these three associations. 

</TEXT>

