<H3> <TI>   Iraq To Close Embassy in Baku </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraq To Close Embassy in Baku </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1162A Baku ZERKALO in Russian 30 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1162A </F>
<F P=104>  Baku ZERKALO </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article under the heading "Panorama": "Iraqi </F>
Embassy in Azerbaijan Is Closing"] 
  [Text] In the course of a meeting with Minister of Foreign 
Affairs of Azerbaijan Hasan Hasanov, Faruq Salman Da'ud, head of 
the Iraqi Embassy in Baku, stated that the Iraqi diplomatic 
mission in Azerbaijan is being temporarily closed because of the 
difficult economic situation that has developed recently in that 
country. As the foreign policy department noted while informing 
the ANS-PRESS agency about this, F.S. Da'ud stressed that in 
view of a shortage of foreign exchange funds in Iraq, the 
government of that country has also been compelled to wind down 
the operation of diplomatic missions in [word illegible], 
Hungary, Romania, Poland, India, and a majority of African 
states. With reference to the significance of reinforcing 
Azerbaijani-Iraqi relations, the diplomat expressed the hope 
that the financial situation of his country will shortly make it 
possible to resume operation of the Iraqi Embassy in Baku. 

</TEXT>

